AB  - The new species Aureliana angustifolia (Solanaceae) from a secondary forest of Juiz de Fora, in southeastern Brazil, is described. It is distinguished by its narrowly lanceolate leaves, by the brief and triangular calyx lobes, and by the subglobose fruits with a thin pericarp. The style length dimorphism with the lack of the stigmatic papillae on the short style suggests that it is an andromonoecious species.
