AB  - This study was carried out from 1985 to 1987, in the mid-southern region of Parana State (25 degrees 52'S, 50 degrees 23'W), with the purpose of recognizing the plant species occuring in an area adjacent to the PETROSIX mine field, as a technical support for reforestation of areas degraded by mining activities. All Pteridophyta, Pinophyta and Magnoliphyta species found fertile were collected during the study period, according to usual collecting and preparing of botanical material techniques and all the identification being made through specialized literature, herbarium research and help from specialists. The study site's vegetation is represented by Mixed Ombrophilous Forest and its respective secondary successional stages, where a total of 307 species were determined, belonging to 76 families, and the ones most species rich were Asteraceae (42), Myrtaceae (20), Rubiaceae (18), Solanaceae (16) and Lauraceae (12), among the phanerogams, and Polypodiaceae (8) among the pteridophytes. Based on floristic comparisons with other Mixed Ombrophilous Forest areas in the same region, the most typical tree species in this type of vegetation are present here.
